We recommended that Management require:
The Municipal Treasurer to conduct complete physical inventory of all PPE owned by the Municipality. To facilitate the inventory taking, Management may require each office to conduct physical count of PPE under their custody and prepare an inventory report that is complete in all particulars for submission to the Municipal Treasurer who in turn will reconcile and verify the same with their present inventory reports;




The Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to: (i) analyze the discrepancies noted and reconcile their records; (ii) effect the necessary adjustments in the books of accounts, if warranted; and (iii) update the Property Cards (PCs) and PPE Ledger Cards (PPELCs) with complete details.

We recommended that Management:

Request for the bank statements for every bank account maintained by the Municipality in each of the depository bank, whether or not the subject bank account had no transaction for the year;

Prepare BRS for every bank account maintained by the Municipality;

Secure a certification on the balances and status from the concerned depository bank on the balances of the bank account number 5325-645-7 maintained in the Development Bank of the Philippines (DBP) and bank account number 0782-1066-43 maintained in the Land Bank of the Philippines (LBP). Thereafter, take the necessary appropriate action in order to update the records of the Municipality;


Require the Municipal Accountant to effect immediately the necessary adjustments relative to the book reconciling items with available supporting documents;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to exert extra effort in locating the documents relative to prior years reconciling items and ensure that book reconciling items will not increase in the succeeding years;

Revert back to the CIB-LCCA the amount of all the stale checks of the Municipality and recognize the corresponding liability account or the government equity account whichever is applicable; and

Communicate to the concerned depository bank regarding the bank errors presented in the BRS in order to arrive at the correct balance of the CIB-LCCA.

